    "html": "<div class=\"beforedestroydocumentation\">\n  <h1 id=\"before-destroy-method\">beforeDestroy() Lifecycle Method</h1>\n  <p>\n    The <code>beforeDestroy()</code> method runs right before a component is destroyed by the Controller.\n    Use it to clean up timers, observers, global listeners, and pending async work.\n  </p>\n\n  <h2 id=\"when-to-use\">When to Use beforeDestroy()</h2>\n  <ul>\n    <li>Cancel intervals, timeouts, and animation frames</li>\n    <li>Abort pending fetch requests</li>\n    <li>Remove global or external event listeners</li>\n    <li>Dispose third-party instances (charts, maps, etc.)</li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <div class=\"before-destroy-example\"></div>\n\n  <h2 id=\"best-practices\">Best Practices</h2>\n  <div class=\"best-practices\"></div>\n\n  <h2 id=\"pitfalls\">Common Pitfalls</h2>\n  <div class=\"pitfalls\"></div>\n</div>\n",
